added.title: Greed is Good?
added.description: When Jestro uses the Book of Greed to rob Auremville of its riches, he also gets Lance's parents as prisoners and these demanding rich folks are too much for even monsters to handle.

added.title: The Book of Monsters Part 2
added.description: After a magical explosion, Jestro discovers that he still has the Book of Monsters and together they decide to attack and destroy the Kingdom. Their monsters seem like too much for the new Knights of Knighton until an old friend emerges in a new form.

added.title: The Black Knight
added.description: When the Knights of Knighton can't defend the outer villages of the kingdom, a mysterious Black Knight appears to take on Jestro and his monsters. Who is he really and is he a new ally or a new foe?

added.title: The Might and the Magic
added.description: Seeing Jestro's monster army about to destroy the King's Castle, Aaron rides off to gather his cohorts. In the meantime, the King and Queen bravely go out to defend the city against the monster menace. Is this the end of Knighton?

added.title: Homecoming Part 1
added.description: When Beast Boy's former team, The Doom Patrol, is in trouble, the Titans must embark on a daring mission to save them. Beast Boy explains this can only mean one thing. The Doom Patrol's greatest foes are back. The Brotherhood of Evil has returned.

added.title: Homecoming Part 2
added.description: The Doom Patrol has been saved but the sinister Brotherhood of Evil is still on the loose. It's just like old times for Beast Boy when he finds himself back on the team for one last mission to stop the Brotherhood once and for all no matter what the cost.

added.title: Trust
added.description: The Brotherhood of Evil has begun its master plan to eliminate all of the young superheroes around the globe starting with honorary Titans Wildebeest and Hotspot. This new threat brings Robin to Morocco. But with an unknown enemy, how can anyone know who to trust?

added.title: For Real
added.description: Control Freak returns to Titans' Tower with the ultimate Titans challenge, a series of events designed specifically to challenge the Teen Titans. But what happens to Control Freak's big plan when he finds himself facing not the real Titans but the Titans East?

added.title: Snow Blind
added.description: While battling a mysterious creature in the wilds of Siberia, Starfire is lost in a blinding snowstorm. A reclusive young soldier named Red Star comes to her aid and the two become fast friends. When Robin and the rest of the Titans arrive, they discover Red Star hides not only a tragic past but a destructive secret.

added.title: Kole
added.description: While in the Arctic Circle, the Teen Titans once again take on Dr. Light. And when an accident sends the Titans through the ice, they discover a new exotic Underworld and two new superheroes, Kole and her caveman sidekick Gnarrk.

added.title: Hide and Seek
added.description: With the other Teen Titans off fighting exciting battles with the Brotherhood of Evil, Raven is left with the worst task of all, transporting three rambunctious future superheroes to safety. But this simple task turns into an adventure in babysitting as Raven and her young charges are chased through the Alps by the Brotherhood of Evil's Monsieur Mallah.

added.title: Lightspeed
added.description: With Titans dispatched across the globe, members of the Hive Five figure they have it made. Unfortunately, their city-wide crime spree is cut short when a new hero in town spoils the fun. Handing him over to the Brotherhood of Evil may score the Hive Five points but actually catching this lightning-fast do-gooder is much harder than it seems.

added.title: Revved Up
added.description: Robin's most prized possession is stolen by the hip hot-rodder Ding Dong Daddy. To get it back, they're going to have to beat him in a cross-country road race. But with Ding Dong Daddy making the rules and a few unexpected rivals joining in the competition, it's anyone's guess who will cross the finish line first!

added.title: Go
added.description: How did Robin meet Starfire? What was Beast Boy's first joke? Why did Cyborg build his sonic cannon? When did Raven first call the Titans her friends? Return to the very beginning and see how it all started from the word go!

added.title: Calling All Titans
added.description: The final game has begun. While the Titans are spread throughout the globe on one last mission, Brotherhood mastermind, the Brain, makes his move. Robin has a strategy of his own but as all the villains begin taking down all the superheroes all at once, will it be enough to save his friends?

added.title: Titans Together
added.description: All seems lost for young heroes across the globe. They have been spread far and wide, their lines of communication have been severed and one by one the Brotherhood of Evil takes them down. But as The Brain claims his victory is assured, one brave hero manages to slip thorough the Brotherhood of Evil's grasp: Beast Boy.

added.title: Things Change
added.description: After months of fighting the Brotherhood of Evil around the globe, the Teen Titans are finally back home. But a walk through the city reveals things are no longer as they remembered. And while Beast Boy wants everything to be just like it was in the past, he has to face the fact that in life things change.

added.title: Episode 257-494
added.description: When Control Freak busts out of jail, throwing him back in should be as easy as clicking a remote. But after Control Freak hotwires some high-end AV equipment and escapes into a TV set, things get a little weird. Can the Titans make their way through the wacky world of television to catch the channel-flipping bad guy? Or will Control Freak make our heroes flip out?

added.title: The Quest
added.description: When Robin is defeated by the malicious martial artist, Kitarou, our hero decides if he wants to be the best, he needs more training. So he embarks on a difficult quest to seek a mysterious, legendary teacher known only as The True Master.

added.title: Birthmark
added.description: Slade is back and this time he's after Raven. The question is why?

added.title: Cyborg the Barbarian
added.description: Cyborg is mysteriously thrown into the distant past and lands in the middle of a barbarian village that needs his help. But with the nearest charging station 5,000 years in the future, Cyborg has no way to recharge and his power supply is dwindling. Can Cyborg get back to his own time before time runs out?

added.title: Employee of the Month
added.description: Beast Boy has only one real dream in life to someday, somehow own a moped. When Robin won't buy him one and Cyborg won't build him one, Beast Boy has only one way to make his dream come true. He has to get a job. But can vegetarian Beast Boy survive working at the Mega Meaty Meat fast food restaurant?

added.title: Troq
added.description: A brave hero from outer space called Val-Yor comes to Earth and asks for the Titans help in defeating an otherworldly menace known as The Locrix. But according to Val-Yor, Starfire may be the real problem.

added.title: The Prophecy
added.description: Why did Slade come back? What is he planning? Ever since the return of their arch-nemesis, the Titans have been searching for answers. But is there something Raven isn't telling them?

added.title: Stranded
added.description: An exciting battle on a distant space station ends with a tremendous explosion that blows the T-Ship apart and sends the Titans flying off in five different directions to crash land on a strange alien world. Will our five shipwrecked heroes ever be able to get back together and find their way home?

added.title: Overdrive
added.description: Cyborg is a guy with a can do attitude. And with the new Maximum 7 processor upgrade driving his circuits, it looks like he can do more than ever before. But when Cyborg meets his multitasking match in the duplicitous Billy Numerous, can Cyborg really push himself to the max?

added.title: Mother Mae-Eye
added.description: Every child needs a mother -- even five superpowered sweeties who live in a giant "T"

added.title: The End Part 1
added.description: The stars are aligned. The sun is in eclipse. All of Slade's labors are about to reach fruition and the Titans are about to face their greatest challenge ever. But is there really any hope of preventing the end of the world?

added.title: The End Part 2
added.description: The stars are aligned. The sun is in eclipse. All of Slade's labors are about to reach fruition and the Titans are about to face their greatest challenge ever. But is there really any hope of preventing the end of the world?

added.title: The End Part 3
added.description: The stars are aligned. The sun is in eclipse. All of Slade's labors are about to reach fruition and the Titans are about to face their greatest challenge ever. But is there really any hope of preventing the end of the world?

added.title: Deception
added.description: School's back in session at the Hive Academy and Gizmo, Jinx and Mammoth are up to something. To find out what, the Titans send Cyborg on a daring undercover mission to infiltrate the academy and blend in as one of their own. Using a holographic cloaking device, Cyborg creates the appearance he is fully human and takes on the persona of Stone, a tough transfer student who can change into a powerful creature of Solid Rock. But when the Academy's mysterious new headmaster, Brother Blood, takes an interest in Stone, will Cyborg's cover be blown?

added.title: X
added.description: When the Titans track down the culprit in a string of recent robberies, our heroes are shocked to find themselves facing a foe they thought they'd never see again: Robin's evil alter ego, the mysterious Red X. Is Robin to blame for Red X's crimes?

added.title: Betrothed
added.description: The Teen Titans take a road trip to Starfire's home planet, Tamaran. But this is no ordinary visit. The Grand Ruler of Tamaran has arranged for Starfire to be married! The Titans try to go along with the strange ways of Starfire's homeworld. But Robin has a hard time believing Starfire really wants to marry someone she's never even met. And when he learns the Grand Ruler is none other than Blackfire, it seems like Starfire's evil sister may be up to her old tricks. Can Robin stop the wedding before it's too late?

added.title: Crash
added.description: When Beast Boy mistakes Cyborg's system recharger for a video game system, he accidentally infects it with a nasty computer virus. The virus quickly spreads to Cyborg himself causing the half-teen, half-machine to go haywire. And the only way to stop the virus is to shrink down to microscopic size and go on a fantastic voyage inside Cyborg. Does Amoeba Beast Boy have the brains to fix Cyborg's brains before a crazed Cyborg destroys the city?

added.title: Haunted
added.description: Ever since the Titans' final confrontation with Slade, Robin has been haunted by one question: is Slade really gone? And when Cinderblock breaks out of jail, Robin finally gets his answer. He sees Slade. Robin goes after him fiercely determined to stop his nemesis once and for all. But when Robin learns Slade is planning to trigger a massive earthquake, it looks like there might be no stopping him this time. Will Robin stop Slade from destroying the city? Or is there more to Slade's plan than meets the eye?

added.title: Spellbound
added.description: There's no one else quite like Raven: dark, somber and undeniably creepy. Even with four friends around her, Raven still manages to feel alone in Titans' Tower until she discovers a charming young wizard named Malchior trapped inside one of her ancient books. Raven finally finds someone who truly understands her. But will her relationship with Malchior threaten her friendship with the Titans?

added.title: Revolution
added.description: The Titans' Forth of July festivities are cut short when Mad Mod crashes the party declaring the American Revolution a Hoax and reclaiming the city for Jolly Old England. And if that wasn't enough, old Mod uses his high-tech cane to steal Robin's youth making King Moddie young again while Robin turns into a withered, dried-up old man. Can the remaining Teen Titans come up with a plan to take back their city and save their leader?

added.title: Wavelength
added.description: Brother Blood is back. And this time, it's personal. Cyborg learns Blood stole his blueprints and the villain is using Cyborg's technology to create a doomsday device. Can Cyborg take charge of the team and lead a mission to stop his arch-enemy? Or will he even get the chance?

added.title: The Beast Within
added.description: When Beast Boy begins turning into an angry aggressive Man Beast against his will, can the Titans save themselves from their savage friend?

added.title: Can I Keep Him
added.description: Starfire adopts a weird mutant silkworm named Silkie as a pet. But when she feeds him some alien food from Tamaran, Silkie has an unexpected and monstrous growth spurt. Can Starfire still keep her beloved worm?

added.title: Bunny Raven...or....How to Make a Titananimal Disappear
added.description: The Amazing Mumbo is up to his old tricks. And when the Titans try to stop the madcap, magician in mid-performance, Mumbo pulls a fast one. With a wave of his wand, he sucks the Titans into his hat, where our heroes discover a strange, magical world of weirdness. But in this world, Mumbo's holding all the cards. In a poof of magic, he changes the Titans into animals and takes away their powers. Can the Titanimals find their way out of the hat before Mubmo makes them disappear forever?

added.title: Titans East Part 1
added.description: Part one of the two-part finale containing the final showdown between Cyborg and Brother Blood and the creation of a new branch of the Titans' team. Titans East, a new tower in a new city with five new members: Aqualad, Bumblebee, Speedy and a pair of high-speed twins known as Mas y Menos.

added.title: Titans East Part 2
added.description: Part two of the finale containing the final showdown between Cyborg and Brother Blood, and the creation of a new branch of the Titans' team. Titans East, a new tower in a new city with five new members: Aqualad, Bumblebee, Speedy and a pair of high-speed twins known as Mas y Menos.

added.title: How Long Is Forever?
added.description: A thief from the future called Warp travels back in time to steal an antique. When the Titans show up, the villain tries to escape. In an effort to catch the crook, Starfire is pulled into his Time Vortex and is hurled 20 years into the future.

added.title: Every Dog Has His Day
added.description: A green alien dog comes to Earth with a flying saucer chasing after it. When the alien dog bumps into green dog Beast Boy, the flying saucer abducts the wrong pooch. And when the Titans spot the alien dog, they mistakenly think it's Beast Boy!

added.title: Terra
added.description: The Titans meet Terra. Gifted with earth-moving abilities, Terra can make rocks fly, mountains crumble and the ground tremble beneath her feet. It seems like she might make a great addition to the team. But Terra has a secret, a terrible secret.

added.title: Only Human
added.description: When Cyborg was a fully human athlete, he loved trying to do more than he thought he could do. He always gave 110%. But now that his muscles are mechanical, Cyborg's limitations are built in. No matter how much he tries, 100% is all he's got.

added.title: Fear Itself
added.description: Raven doesn't do fear. Or at least, that's what she wants you to think. But when a ghostly, unknown force starts hunting down the Titans one by one, Titans' Tower turns into a house of horrors and even Raven gets rattled.

added.title: Date with Destiny
added.description: Criminal Killer Moth threatens to destroy the city unless Robin takes his daughter Kitten to her junior prom. While the Titans are scouring the city in the search of Moth's hideout, Robin has no choice but to go along with the villain's demand.

added.title: Transformation
added.description: The beautiful alien Starfire has never thought much about her looks. But when a strange red bump appears on her forehead, Starfire becomes concerned. Raven tells her not to worry. It's probably just a zit. Or is it?

added.title: Titan Rising
added.description: Terra returns to Titans' Tower and she's ready to join the team. After what happened to the last time they saw her, the Titans aren't sure that's such a good idea. Raven is positive it's not. Robin reminds her everyone deserves a second chance.

added.title: Winner Take All
added.description: Robin, Cyborg and Beast Boy are transported to an alternate dimension. There, the mysterious Master of Games invites our heroes and five other super-powered teens to participate in a competition: The Tournament of Heroes.

added.title: Betrayal
added.description: After weeks as a Teen Titan, Terra has everything she ever wanted: a nice home, good friends and even a little romance with Beast Boy. Everything seems perfect but is it?

added.title: Fractured
added.description: When Robin wrecks the R-Cycle while pursuing a thug named Johnny Rancid, he winds up with his arm in a cast and doubt in himself. He gets a helpful visit from his Number One Fan: a short weirdo from another dimension known as Larry the Titan!

added.title: Aftershock Part 1
added.description: A long lost friend of the Titans returns with a vengeance and Slade orders Overload, Cinderblock and Plasmus to launch a series of sinister attacks all over the city. Can our heroes stop three monsters, Slade and their newest enemies?

added.title: Aftershock Part 2
added.description: In a world without Titans, Slade has taken control of everything: the streets, the city and the heart of his young Apprentice. But are our heroes really gone?

added.title: Final Exam
added.description: The Hive Academy unveils its top graduates: Gizmo, Mammoth and Jinx. Before Slade will hire the new Hive Agents, he requires they pass one final exam: they must destroy the Teen Titans.

added.title: Sisters
added.description: When an alien probe shows up to haul Starfire away, Starfire has no idea why it came. And when Starfire's sister, Blackfire, shows up to visit, Starfire just wishes she would leave. Blackfire's wild, cool and hip, everything Starfire's not.

added.title: Divide and Conquer
added.description: Cinderblock busts into prison and the Teen Titans show up to stop a jailbreak. But when Robin and Cyborg's big sonic boom maneuver goes awry, the bad guys get away and the boys blame each other.

added.title: Forces of Nature
added.description: Dark Ominous clouds blow in from the East, bringing Thunder and Lightning with them: two forces of nature made flesh into the form of costumed super-teens. The stormy brothers aren't evil. They're just looking for a good time.

added.title: The Sum of His Parts
added.description: A day of fun in the park is cut short when Cyborg suddenly freezes like a statue. His power cell is dying. While the problem is easily fixed with a new battery, Cyborg is reminded he's not completely human.

added.title: Nevermore
added.description: When a battle with Dr. Light pushes Raven over the edge, the Titans see a side of their friend they've never seen before: her temper. After Raven's creepy tantrum leaves Dr. Light begging for mercy, Beast Boy isn't quite sure how to treat her.

added.title: Switched
added.description: Starfire doesn't understand Raven's repression. Raven can't deal with Starfire's emotional outbursts. When Puppet King imprisons Robin, Cyborg and Beast Boy inside wooden puppets, the girls have to understand each other if they want to survive.

added.title: Deep Six
added.description: When a mysterious villain makes off with dangerous toxic waste, the Teen Titans hop into the T-Sub and go on an undersea adventure to find out what is up and put a stop to it.

added.title: Mask
added.description: Slade sends a team of robotic commandos to steal a high-tech chip. The Titans stop the robbery but Starfire nearly gets hurt in the process. Robin becomes more determined than ever to find out who Slade is and what he's planning.

added.title: Mad Mod
added.description: The Teen Titans awake to find themselves captured prisoners of Mad Mod. Miffed at the way the Titans disrespect their elders and interfere with the toils of hard working criminals, Mad Mod has decided to teach the teens a lesson.

added.title: Apprentice Part 1
added.description: Who is Slade? What is he planning? The questions keeping Robin awake at night are about to be answered. Slade contacts the Teen Titans and unveils his master plan: A Chronoton Detonator, a high-tech device has the ability to stop time forever.

added.title: Apprentice Part 2
added.description: With no signs of Robin since Slade's Chronoton Detonator turned out to be a fake, the four remaining Teen Titans search the city for their missing leader. But their search is cut short when the Titan signal alerts them to a new villain in town. And when they arrive on the scene at a high-tech defense lab, they are shocked to discover this new villain is none other than Robin himself wearing a sinister new Slade insignia villain costume.

added.title: Car Trouble
added.description: Cyborg finished building the car of his dreams: the ultra-high-tech T-Car! Cyborg shows off his car to the Titans. Before Cyborg can take his car out for a spin, the Titans are called to a superstore where Overload is wreaking havoc.

added.title: Elf Pets: Santa's St. Bernards Save Christmas
added.description: Inside the town of Bellville, Jonah, a small local thrift shop owner struggles to keep his modest business afloat while surrounded by townsfolk who have forgotten that the true spirit of Christmas involves a generous heart. Little do they know that their lack of Christmas cheer is affecting Santa Claus and keeping him from being magical at the North Pole. Without Christmas magic, the sleigh doesn't glide, toys don't get made, and the Christmas Eve flight could be delayed. Join Santa, his scout elf friends, and all of the Elf Pets St. Bernard pups as they inspire Jonah's children to raise Christmas cheer, change their community for the better, and help keep Christmas magical at the North Pole.

added.title: Lego: Batman the Movie: DC Super Heroes Unite
added.description: When the Joker and Lex Luthor form an alliance, Batman must team up with the Justice League in order to stop them.

added.title: Lego DC Comics Super Heroes: The Flash
added.description: The morning sun shines on the jewel of the Metropolis skyline, The Daily Planet building. But when The Joker decides this building needs a renovation, it's time to sound the Trouble Alert because all bricks are about to break loose! The Justice League leaps into action, but as the battle is brewing against The Joker, something goes haywire with The Flash's powers, causing him to get caught in a repeating time loop. Even stranger is the yellow-clad Reverse Flash taunting him at every turn. It will take all of Flash's speed, a little magic and the helping hands and paws of the Justice League's new recruits, The Atom, Krypto the Superdog and Ace the Bat-Hound, to break the cycle and save Metropolis.

added.title: Lego Justice League: Gotham City Breakout
added.description: When Batman is dragged on vacation by a well-meaning Nightwing and Batgirl, things go terribly awry for the Bat family and they end up in a lost underground world where Bane and Deathstroke plan on using an inhuman army to conquer the surface world. Meanwhile, Gotham City is being babysat by Superman and Robin, who find they're up to their necks in trouble when the Joker stages a massive criminal breakout from Arkham Asylum!

added.title: Back to School
added.description: When the Nexo Knights are sloppy in a fight with Jestro, Merlok 2.0 sends them back to the Knights' Academy. Not only for a brush-up but to find out what Jestro is after in its hallowed halls.

added.title: The Book of Obsession
added.description: The Knights are tasked with protecting the King's valuable Ned Knights comic book during the Bookingheim Knight-a-Con. But with all the costumed kids there, will they recognize the real Jestro and Book of Monsters coming to get them?

added.title: The King's Tournament
added.description: Rival to the King, Jorah Tightwad thinks his knights, the Tighty Knighties, are easily better than the Nexo Knights, so he challenges King Halbert to prove who's better during the King's Birthday Tournament.

added.title: Monster Chef
added.description: Axl and Chef Éclair must enter a cooking contest to try to keep Jestro from getting the hottest chili recipe in the realm.

added.title: Knight Out
added.description: When the other Nexo Knights decide they need a vacation from Clay, they send him on a holiday not knowing he's going to a resort that houses an evil book or that Jestro will be heading there too.

added.title: Saturday Knight Fever
added.description: The Book of Monsters catching a cold means trouble for the Nexo Knights when he can create an entirely new kind of snotty monster.

added.title: Open Mike Knight
added.description: The Book of Betrayal leads Jestro and his Monsters to Funnyton, the funniest town in the kingdom. When they Knights arrive to capture him, they discover to their shock that Jestro and the Book of Monsters are now the town's top comedians!

added.title: The Fortrex and the Furious
added.description: In a massive chase around Knighton, the Nexo Knights attempt to keep the Book of Betrayal out of the Book of Monster's grip. But the evil book is persistent. Will he get the final piece of his evil puzzle?

added.title: Kingdom of Heroes
added.description: The Book of Monsters, having the final pieces of his evil plan in place, tries to take human form. Can the Nexo Knights and Merlok 2.0 stop the greatest threat they've ever faced? Or will the kingdom be plunged into darkness forever.

added.title: The Book of Monsters Part 1
added.description: During the graduation ceremony for the new Knights of Knighton, Jestro the jester is ridiculed for his terrible, uh, jestring. Distraught, he's seduced by the powerful and evil Book of Monsters until Merlok the Magician tries to stop Jestro by using his most powerful magic spell.

added.title: The Power of Merlok
added.description: When Jestro and the Book of Monsters start using their monsters to ravage the countryside, the Knights get an awesome new HQ to fight him, the mighty, powerful Rolling Castle known as the Fortrex.

added.title: The Knights' Code
added.description: Clay and Lance tussle over who should lead the Knights and protect the King who's toddles off on a PR tour of the kingdom. While fighting off Jestro and his monsters, Lance realizes that nobody knows the Knights' Code like Cla.

added.title: Fright Knight
added.description: The Knights explore a strange forest looking for a Book when Jesto unleashes the Book of Fear on them and a new monster, Whiparella, uses her minions to induce the Knights' worst knightmares.

added.title: The Golden Castle
added.description: When Lance stars in a movie about the Knights, the Book of Monsters want to eat the script to learn more about modern society. Jestro uses his spy, Lavaria, to infiltrate the set and attack the Knights.

added.title: The Maze of Amazement
added.description: Jestro and the Knights are both trying to get the Book of Deception. But the book has used its powers to create a powerful maze in the Hill Country, near Axl's home, and it's a race to complete the maze and get the Boo.

added.title: The Book of Total Badness
added.description: Jestro uses the baddest book yet, the Book of Destruction, to make monsters that capture the Knights one-by-one so that he can turn his attention to attacking the King's Castle.
